        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 5:00PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 500 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Leachville, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Blytheville, Gosnell, Manila, Leachville, Hornersville, Dell,
Holland, Jolliff Store, Dearman, Calumet, Carmi, Whisp, Buckeye,
Arkmo, Noland, Roseland, Stark City, Happy Corners, Big Lake, and
Burton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
